5:
Lying around in bed all day is
wonderful, but aimlessly strolling
through town isn't half bad either!
8:
That's great and all, but are you sure
it's okay for someone as famous as
you to be out here? If someone
recognizes you...
12:
It should be fine. The people of
Palpebra aren't all that pious. They
probably don't even know who I am!
15:
Well, well, if it isn't our favorite saint!
Are you taking another day off
again, miss? Don't overdo it!
18: So much for not being recognized.
23:
I mean, it happens occasionally, I
suppose!
27:
There seems to be a commotion
over there... Let's go take a look!
31:
How many times must I tell you!
That light you call "magic" is actually
the guidance of the Stars! It's a
miracle of the Church of Farlana!
32:
We cannot permit those who are not
Starseekers—much less ruffians like
you—to gallivant around using such
holy light! It is blasphemy!
34:
Huh? Your religion doesn't mean
crap to me, old man. I'm not in the
mood to be lectured by some
preacher who knows nothing about
the world.
37:
Hmm, you see this sort of thing from
time to time. People from the church
sometimes get into arguments with
adventurers.
40:
They must not be used to how
things work here in Palpebra. The
rules of the Farlands and other
parishes don't apply to the
adventurers here...
42:
I have read many reports describing
clashes between locals and... those
who place great importance on
upholding our doctrine.
46:
Well, what are we gonna do about
it? Can you step in and... I don't
know, arbitrate?
51:
No, I don't think I will... I'm just a
figurehead, remember? If I were to
butt in, it would only make matters
worse.
55:
I see... If you were to intervene, it
could further fan the flames.
59:
Yes. As a figurehead, it's my duty to
be a beacon for all people, equally. I
cannot take sides or involve myself
in conflicts.
75:
We're getting reports that there was
a quake at the Kaleidoscope and a
whole ton of monsters just suddenly
appeared!
78:
They're about to penetrate our
defensive perimeter... There's even
the chance they might make their
way into the city!
80:
A whole host of adventurers have
already assembled and are
heading to the Kaleidoscope. They
need help—we need to start
evacuations!
87:
Lady Orvelle?! What are you doing in
a place like this?
90:
This is neither the time nor place. We
must hurry.
91:
Please start taking care of the
wounded. Sound the alarm across
town and alert everyone you can!
106:
Don't let your guard down! Another
wave is coming in.
109: Be at ease, you are safe now!
113: N-no... I think we were the last.
117:
Understood. You can leave the rest
to us!
121:
O sacred Light! Grant us the
guidance of the Stars, that we may
find a way to triumph over this
adversity!
137:
Phew. That should take care of most
of the remaining monsters!
140:
Whoooa! Little Miss Saint, you're
incredible!
142:
And here I thought you were just
slacking off the whole time. Looks
like you lived up to your title!
144:
What did you just call her? Watch
your tongue when you address Lady
Orvelle! She may be a bit... rough
around the edges, but she is a
canonized Saint!
146:
Heh, you're right. My bad! Either way,
she's really something!
147:
Hmm... Well, I suppose it's to be
commended that a boorish
adventurer like you can come to
understand that much.
149:
Lady Orvelle is the very
manifestation of the miracles the
Stars are capable of!
151:
Mhm. Thanks, by the way. For using
your healing magic—er, I mean your
healing "light power" or whatever.
You saved a buddy of mine.
153:
Ah, yes, well... Though your attitude
and demeanor leaves much to be
desired, I cannot deny your fighting
prowess.
156:
Well, look at that. They're starting to
see eye to eye! A little bit, at least.
159:
Heh. These guys aren't all that
complicated after all.
163:
Any progress is welcome. This is far
better than having them snarling at
each other on the streets.
167:
Lady Stella... You asked me earlier if
it was difficult...
170:
To tell you the truth, it is. Very.
Honestly, I'm probably losing hair
'cause of all the stress!
174:
But... If my role as a figurehead for
the church allows people to come
together like this, to overlook their
differences...
176:
Then I think it's worth it. It drives to
me keep working hard to fulfill my
role as a saint.
179: I'm very glad to hear that.
187:
That being said! I have no intention
of sacrificing my ME time! If you
don't mind, I'll be going to Starview
Village and indulging myself!
190:
Um... That's great and all, but could
you loaf around somewhere other
than my room this time?
196:
Whaaat? How could you say
something like that, Alk!
199:
H-huh? That's a perfectly normal
request! Okay, how about we make
you another pillow? Just one more
trip up the mountain!
208:
AAH! How does that even work? Just
THINKING about it makes you want
to throw up? Are you okay?!
